J2Xcode is a Ruby script to synchronize Java sources with Xcode using Google's j2objc tool. It compares the supplied source files with a cache, performs incremental translation, and updates the Xcode project accordingly.

Usage: ruby j2xcode.rb '/path/to/j2objc' '--j2objc-options' '/path/to/xcode/proj/file.xcodeproj' 'MyTarget' '/path/to/java/src::com/company/app' '/path/to/java/src::net/company2/file.java' ...

Under the Xcode project folder, a folder named "Java" will be created and used for caching and generated sources. You can remove the folder anytime if something goes wrong with synchronization.

Requirements:
https://github.com/CocoaPods/Xcodeproj

